entity.name: Trump and his company sued for alleged fraud
entity.description: On Wednesday, New York Attorney General Letitia James filed a civil lawsuit against former president Donald Trump, the Trump Organization and three of his adult children for fraud and misrepresentation of assets. The lawsuit alleges that the Trump Organization wrongfully prepared Trump’s annual financial statements from 2011 to 2021 and also names Trump’s sons Donald Trump Jr. and Eric Trump and his daughter Ivanka Trump as defendants. The Trump Organization called the allegations “baseless,” Reuters reports.

entity.name: Winter storm Landon moves across the US, bringing ice and snow
entity.description: A major winter storm that already cut power to about 350,000 homes and businesses from Texas to the Ohio Valley is set to leave Pennsylvania and New England glazed in ice and smothered in snow on Friday, The Associated Press reports. The National Weather Service said the storm will produce heavy snow, treacherous ice accumulations and bitter cold in the Northeast on Friday, with scattered showers and possible thunderstorms in the Southeast. Keep it here for the latest.

entity.name: Tornado strikes New Orleans, killing at least one and leaving thousands without power
entity.description: A tornado tore through parts of New Orleans and its suburbs Tuesday night, ripping down power lines and scattering debris. St. Bernard Parish Sheriff Jimmy Pohlmann said one person was confirmed dead and multiple others were injured in the suburb. Other tornadoes spawned by the same storm system hit parts of Texas and Oklahoma, while heavy rain and powerful winds were reported in Louisiana, Mississippi and Alabama. National Weather Service forecasters warned some five million people in the region could see dangerous weather.
